{% set pageTitle = "What's new" %}
{% set pageDescription = "Find out what's happening with the service manual." %}
{% set pageSection = "What's new" %}
{% set landingPage = true %}

{% extends "layouts/app-layout.njk" %}

{% block bodyContent %}

  <h2>Latest updates</h2>

  <h3>August 2025</h3>
  <table class="nhsuk-table">
    <caption class="nhsuk-table__caption nhsuk-u-visually-hidden">Updates to the service manual in August 2025</caption>
    <thead class="nhsuk-table__head">
      <tr class="nhsuk-table__row">
        <th class="nhsuk-table__header" scope="col" style="width: 25%;">Section</th>
        <th class="nhsuk-table__header" scope="col">Update</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="nhsuk-table__body">
      <tr>
        <td class="nhsuk-table__cell">Design system</td>
        <td class="nhsuk-table__cell">
          <p>Added new <a href="/design-system/components/header#account-information-and-links">account information and links variant of header component</a>.</p>
          <p><a href="/design-system/components/header">Header</a> design updates include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>new feature to highlight current page in the navigation menu</li>
            <li>improved NHS logo focus state</li>
            <li>removing home link that was automatically added on small screens</li>
            <li>wrapping service name onto a new line only when there is not enough space to show it beside the NHS logo</li>
            <li>left-aligning navigation items by default</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Added new <a href="/design-system/components/notification-banner">notification banners component</a></p>
          <p>Added new profile icon to <a href="/design-system/styles/icons">icons page</a></p>
          <p>Added new styling for <a href="/design-system/components/buttons#grouping-buttons">grouping buttons</a></p>
          <p>Changed <a href="/design-system/components/buttons">button component</a> styling to make buttons full width on small screens, which aligns with GOV.UK and NHS App</p>
          <p>Updated <a href="/design-system/components/footer">footer component</a> and examples</p>
          <p>Updated guidance for using Nunjucks in <a href="/design-system/production#using-nunjucks-macros">production code</a> on NHS.UK frontend v10.x</p>
          <p>Added more links to image libraries for <a href="/content/inclusive-content/skin-symptoms">inclusive skin symptoms</a></p>
          <p>Updated guidance on <a href="/design-system/styles/colour">colour variables</a> to use 'colour' spelling instead of 'color'</p>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p><a href="/whats-new/updates">See all updates</a></p>

  <h2>Latest blog posts</h2>
  <p>Posts by the service manual team and community.</p>

  <div class="nhsuk-grid-row nhsuk-card-group">
    <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-one-half nhsuk-card-group__item">
      <div class="nhsuk-card nhsuk-card--clickable">
        <img class="nhsuk-card__img" src="/assets/blog-prototype-kit.png" alt="">
        <div class="nhsuk-card__content">
          <h3 class="nhsuk-card__heading"><a href="https://digital.nhs.uk/blog/design-matters/2025/why-we-are-reinvesting-in-the-nhs-prototype-kit">Why we are reinvesting in the NHS prototype kit</a></h3>
          <p class="nhsuk-card__metadata nhsuk-body-s nhsuk-u-secondary-text-colour nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-0"><span class="nhsuk-u-visually-hidden">Published on: </span>21 July 2025</p>
          <p class="nhsuk-card__metadata nhsuk-body-s nhsuk-u-font-weight-bold">NHS England Design Matters blog</p>
          <p class="nhsuk-card__description">Frankie Roberto and Mike Gallagher explain why we revived the NHS prototype kit, the benefits of prototyping in code and how digital teams in the NHS can get started using it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-one-half nhsuk-card-group__item">
      <div class="nhsuk-card nhsuk-card--clickable">
        <img class="nhsuk-card__img" src="/assets/blog-domestic-abuse.jpg" alt="">
        <div class="nhsuk-card__content">
          <h3 class="nhsuk-card__heading"><a href="https://digital.nhs.uk/blog/design-matters/2025/mitigating-the-risks-of-domestic-abuse">Mitigating the risks of domestic abuse</a></h3>
          </h3>
          <p class="nhsuk-card__metadata nhsuk-body-s nhsuk-u-secondary-text-colour nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-0"><span class="nhsuk-u-visually-hidden">Published on: </span>21 May 2025</p>
          <p class="nhsuk-card__metadata nhsuk-body-s nhsuk-u-font-weight-bold">NHS England Design Matters blog</p>
          <p class="nhsuk-card__description">Emma Swift and Zuzanna Lito explain how we've updated the NHS service standard to make sure teams building online services are more aware and responsive to the risks of domestic abuse and coercive control.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

